ha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Closed Haidilao Hotpot restaurant with young man and old woman in face masks walking by\" data-id=\"1212269797\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"></p> <p class=\"item-credits\">SCQBJ-JZ</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Want Some Hotpot? Haidilao Is Coming to You</h2> <p>With a relatively small presence in North America, don\u2019t be surprised if you\u2019ve never heard of <a href=\"https://www.haidilao-inc.com/sg\" rel=\"nofollow\">Haidilao</a>, a leading Chinese restaurant brand that operates hot pot restaurants. It is controlled by</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1212269797/image_1212269797.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742626-super-hi-international-a-steaming-hotpot-worth-the-wait", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 18:08:01"}, {"id": "4742647", "title": "Softish U.S. Jobs Report Favors A December Rate Cut", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"glowing graph 2\" data-id=\"1363842522\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1122px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Jonathan Kitchen</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>By <a href=\"https://think.ing.com/author/james-knightley/\" rel=\"nofollow\">James Knightley </a></em></p> <p></p> <h2>227k jobs added, but remember to factor in strikes and Hurricane Milton haha</h2> <p>US non-farm payrolls have come in at 227k for November, very close to the 220k consensus. There were 56k of upward revisions to</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1363842522/image_1363842522.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742647-softish-us-jobs-report-favors-december-rate-cut", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 18:04:00"}, {"id": "4742625", "title": "Moody's: Overvalued But Still A Hold", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1767263173/image_1767263173.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Gas gauge having indicator of financial credit ratings and having a pointer near AAA rating. Illustration of the concept of commercial and personal credit scores\" data-id=\"1767263173\" data-type=\"getty-image\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Dragon Claws</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2><strong>Overview</strong></h2> <p>Moody's (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MCO\" title=\"Moody's Corporation\">MCO</a></span>) has had a phenomenal return year to date up about 30%, but valuation puts into question what investors should do with their shares. In this article, I want to give some insight into what Moody's does, the business</p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742625-moodys-overvalued-but-still-a-hold", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 18:01:11"}, {"id": "4742640", "title": "Why Gold Could Rally In 2025 Despite Recent Weakness", "description": "<p></p> <p>The price of gold has been one of the best-performing commodities, year to date. Hussein Allidina, Managing Director and Head of Commodities at TD Asset Management, explains why he sees the precious metal pushing even higher into the new year.</p> <h2>Transcript</h2> <p><strong>Greg Bonnell:</strong> Gold has pulled back from its record highs in the wake of the US election. But are there still catalysts that could push the precious metal higher in 2025?</p> <p>Joining us now to discuss, Hussein Allidina, Managing Director and Head of Commodities with TD Asset Management. Hussein, always good to have you on the program.</p> <p><strong>Hussein Allidina:</strong> Thanks for having me, Greg.</p> <p><strong>Greg Bonnell:</strong> Interesting year for gold. You and I have had many discussions about gold this year. We have seen the pullback. Walk us through what we have seen. Why are we at this position right now with gold?</p> <p><strong>Hussein Allidina:</strong> Yeah. Gold has reached many nominal highs this year. We did pull back following the election in the US on the strength in the dollar. I ultimately think that gold does move higher over the course of 2025, 2026.</p> <p>And structurally-- we've talked about this before-- if we look at central banks in the emerging market, they hold a lot of fiat currency, especially relative to their peers in the OECD. If you look at gold holdings in the US, Germany, and France, etc., they're materially higher as a percentage of their reserves relative to the fiat that they hold.</p> <p>If we look in the emerging market, most of their reserves are in US dollars, euros, IMF special drawing rights. And we have seen a diversification out of that paper, frankly, into gold. And I don't think that changes. I think it takes multiple years to get to the levels that you see in the OECD. So that structural demand for gold, I think, will</p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742640-why-gold-could-rally-2025-despite-recent-weakness", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 17:55:00"}]}